			<title>First Post</title>
			<description>This post serves as a “changelog” and to show you step-by-step how I built NiceCSS.</description>
			<author>oldpcdev</author>
			<link>https://oldpcdev.github.io/nicecss/articles/2023/02/first-post-html</link>
			<pubDate>Sat, 25 Feb 2023 11:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
			<content>
				<h1>First Post</h1>

				<p>This post serves as a “changelog” and to show you step-by-step how I built NiceCSS.</p>

				<p>It took a lot of work to do it all.</p>

				<h2>Version 0.0.1.xy: Getting Started</h2>

				<p>I am ashamed of this version. In my head it seemed innovative, but in practice it was horrible and I had to rebuild it again, changing everything until I reached the BrownLooks theme.</p>

				<p>Unfortunately, I didn't take screenshots. and I shall have to say right here what it looked like. The header was 30px high and 100px wide, was at the top of the screen, and had a light red to dark red gradient background. It had a banner with a bokeh background and the content was underneath it. It was terrible, you could barely see the sidebar.</p>

				<h2>Version 0.0.2.xy - 0.0.6.xy: Towards perfection</h2>

				<p>These versions were built at the last minute and I didn't sleep for a LONG time. But in the end, they were almost perfect.</p>

				<p>The 0.0.2.xy and 0.0.3.xy were the ones that defined the design of the site. I drew everything in GIMP.</p>

				<p>0.0.4 .xy- 0.0.6.xy Focused on details like the logo, icons and home page. Fixed several mini bugs. 0.0.5 was the version with the most sub-versions.</p>

				<p>No screenshots too.</p>

				<h2>Version 0.0.7.xy - 0.0.8.xy: No new ideas</h2>

				<p>These versions aren't special and didn't bring almost anything new, just a redesign of the logo, the stylization of the posts. and fixed (many) bugs in CSS.</p>
				
				<div class="img_box">
					<img src="../../../img/v0.0.8.8.jpg" alt="v0.0.8 screenshot">
					<p>Screenshot of the 0.0.8 version</p>
				</div>

				<h2>Version 0.0.9.xy - 0.1.0: Calm is the key to perfection</h2>

				<p>An (almost) happy ending for NiceCSS. What's new are bug fixes and the NiceCSS upload on GitHub Pages.</p>

				<p>Thanks to <a href="https://www.svgrepo.com/collection/instructure-ui-filled-interface-icons/" target="_blank">instructure-ui</a> for the icons and to <a href="https://www.svgrepo.com/svg/500728 /umbrella" target="_blank">element-plus</a> by the umbrella of the logo. All fonts came from Google Fonts.</p>
			</content>
